&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Mission Brief&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;As part of the Launch Vehicle AIT (Assembly, Integration, and Testing) team, you will be responsible for ensuring smooth, efficient, and timely integration activities. In addition, you will be participating in the change management process and work together with relevant stakeholders to drive up key performance indicators (KPIs) and follow-up on non-conformities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW114497174 BCX8&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun CommentStart CommentHighlightPipeRest CommentHighlightRest SCXW114497174 BCX8&quot;&gt;Your Role in Our Space Mission&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create, maintain, and optimize the launch vehicle AIT workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage operational interfaces of the launcher integration team like the Testing, Logistics or Quality Assurance teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and improve the vehicle integration timeline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create efficient tooling to plan, monitor, and optimize launcher integration activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in and drive engineering change management processes concerning launcher integration topics from initial change request through final hardware implementation on flight and nonflight systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a key contributor to the non‑conformance process by assessing criticality, defining scope of impact, and developing/validating corrective and preventive actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as AIT representative to internal stakeholders—including Design Engineering, Launch Operations, and Production—ensuring AIT requirements are understood and integrated into cross-functional decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, lead, and implement internal process improvements aimed at increasing efficiency, reducing rework, and strengthening data flow within AIT.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure safe execution of launcher integration activities by implementing PPE, ESD, and HSE rules together with the HSE team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and realise concepts for AIT facilities across all Isar Aerospace sites.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;EOP CommentHighlightPipeRest SCXW114497174 BCX8&quot; data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:6,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:6,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:360}&quot;&gt;Qualification Checklist &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BSc/MSc in Mechanical/Aerospace Engineering or similar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong drive for continuous improvement and strong communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in bottleneck analysis, line balancing methods, and OEE calculation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive experience in project management including setup, maintenance, and reporting of timelines, KPIs, and processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in assembly and testing of complex systems (medical, aerospace, automotive or similar)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean, organized, and structured way of work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge in Python, C++, or similar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of CAD software&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent in English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Bonus Skills&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic understanding of common systems within the aerospace industry (mechanics, avionics, pressurized systems, engines)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Benefits&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employee Participatio

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Mission Brief&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;As AIT Technician, you will join us on the arctic island of Andøya, and – as part of a small local AIT team – support onsite assembly, integration, test, and launch activities. Together with our dynamic multinational AIT and design teams based in Germany, and the local operations crew you will ensure flawless and timely delivery of flight hardware, and smooth conduction or test and launch campaigns.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW114497174 BCX8&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun CommentStart CommentHighlightPipeRest CommentHighlightRest SCXW114497174 BCX8&quot;&gt;Your Role in Our Space Mission&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun CommentHighlightRest SCXW114497174 BCX8&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;EOP CommentHighlightPipeRest SCXW114497174 BCX8&quot; data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:6,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:6,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:360}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shaping the launch site:&lt;/strong&gt; Continuously improve the AIT infrastructure, and help develop it to compete with world class AIT facilities around the globe&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;High-Precision Assembly:&lt;/strong&gt; Precise assembly of advanced space components&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Machining Carbon Fiber Composites:&lt;/strong&gt; Working with cutting-edge carbon fibre materials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Component and Assembly Testing:&lt;/strong&gt; Validating the functionality of individual parts and complete assemblies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Test and Launch Support:&lt;/strong&gt; Assisting in setting up and preparing the flight hardware for stage testing and launch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;High Cleanliness Standards&lt;/strong&gt;: Maintaining high cleanliness standards to ensure component integrity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Detailed Documentation: &lt;/strong&gt;Accurately documenting work processes to maintain high standards and quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compliance with Standards:&lt;/strong&gt; Ensuring adherence to industry standards and regulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Process Improvement:&lt;/strong&gt; Contributing to continuous process improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;EOP CommentHighlightPipeRest SCXW114497174 BCX8&quot; data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:6,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:6,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:360}&quot;&gt;Qualification Checklist&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completed vocational training as an aircraft mechanic specializing in production engineering, maintenance, engineering or comparable training in accordance with the requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Several years of professional experience in the field of aviation and/or aerospace&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent teamwork&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of gas/fluid bolting techniques&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good drawing skills, spatial awareness and good technical understanding&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness for occasional assembly work at different locations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High attention to detail and quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work under pressure and in a highly dynamic environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foundational knowledge of computer and software applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Well organized mode of working&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Physical dexterity is required as working in confined spaces is necessary (including

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Your Mission&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:6,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:6,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:360}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;Your main objective will be to work hands-on with our Data Platform, which consolidates all structured and unstructured test, flight, and process data from across the company. Your work will empower data-driven decisions in various departments and enable us to generate valuable insights from cross-departmental data.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:6,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:6,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:360}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
