&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Mission Brief&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW114497174 BCX8&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun CommentStart CommentHighlightPipeRest CommentHighlightRest SCXW114497174 BCX8&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;As part of the Guidance, Navigation &amp;amp; Control (GNC) team, you will lead mission analysis activities for upcoming flights and play a key role in ensuring mission success from early design through flight operations. You will be responsible for maintaining, utilizing, and continuously improving the company&#39;s high-fidelity 6DoF simulation environment, which serves as the primary tool for trajectory, performance, and mission analyses.&amp;nbsp;In addition, you will shape and enhance mission analysis processes, develop supporting tools and automation, and contribute to a robust CI/CD framework that enables efficient and reliable simulation and verification workflows&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW114497174 BCX8&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun CommentStart CommentHighlightPipeRest CommentHighlightRest SCXW114497174 BCX8&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW114497174 BCX8&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun CommentStart CommentHighlightPipeRest CommentHighlightRest SCXW114497174 BCX8&quot;&gt;Your Role in Our Space Mission&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;EOP CommentHighlightPipeRest SCXW114497174 BCX8&quot; data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:6,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:6,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:360}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead mission analysis activities for upcoming launch missions, including performance assessment, trajectory evaluation, and flight readiness analyses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and manage the technical data interfaces with multidisciplinary teams, including Propulsion, Structures, and Mission &amp;amp; Launch Operations (MLO)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, execute, and analyze Monte Carlo simulations to assess vehicle performance, robustness, and mission success probabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain, improve, and extend the 6DoF and 3DoF simulation environments, ensuring accuracy, reliability, and traceability of analysis results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support mission-specific trajectory design and optimization efforts using both high-fidelity and reduced-order simulation tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain automated analysis pipelines, report generation tools, and post-processing frameworks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, implement, and maintain unit and integration tests to support automated verification within the CI/CD toolchain&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead mission analysis contributions to regulatory and flight licensing activities, including preparation of required analysis documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;Own the payload controller functionality and serve as the primary GNC interface to the Mission &amp;amp; Launch Operations team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;Contribute to the continuous improvement of mission analysis methodologies, processes, and documentation standards across the organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
